Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2025 15:40:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] QSDK:CP: wifi:ath12k: Add support for WSI bypass remap
 and debugfs interface

This patchset introduces support for WSI bypass remap, allowing
users to remove and re-add targets from the WSI hardwire to
optimize power consumption.

Key changes include:

1. Creation and handling of a debugfs entry to retrieve the remap type
   for a specific device.
2. Cleanup of all ML peers using the low_ack command.
3. Removal of legacy clients on devices undergoing bypass.

These changes facilitate MLO teardown via UMAC reset, enabling firmware
to decouple cleanly from the remapped device.

Patch-dependency:
	0461-0001-QSDK-Platform-Add-support-for-MLO-reconfig-QMI-messa.patch
	0461-0002-QSDK-Platform-WSI-bypass-feature-support.patch
